Bring a #saucepan{} of water up to the boil with @salt{0.5%tsp} for the pasta.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all).

Pick the @rosemary{1/2%sprig} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

Cut @speciality mushroom mix{150%g} into roughly 2cm pieces or separate the mushrooms from their stalks.

When the water is boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{200%g} and cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}, pop back in the pan and drizzle with @oil{1%tbsp} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

== Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{1%tsp} in a #medium sauce pan{} on medium-high heat.

When hot, add the rosemary and half the garlic. Cook stirring frequently for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @water{200%ml} and @wild mushroom paste{1}, stir to dissolve and bring to a boil.

Add the @creme fraiche{75%g} to your sauce, stir to combine and bring to a simmer.

Lower the heat and simmer until you have a rich, creamy sauce, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: Add a splash more water if the sauce is a little thick.

Remove from the heat.

== Mushrooms ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{1%tsp} in another #large frying pan{} on a medium-high heat.

When hot, add the exotic mushrooms and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook stirring frequently until starting to soften and turn golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once golden, add the remaining garlic and cook stirring frequently for ~{1%minute}. Remove from the heat.

== To Serve ==

When ready to serve, add the cooked rigatoni to your creamy sauce, mix together and re-heat until everything is piping hot.

Share between your #bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the chopped parsley and top with the garlicky mushrooms. Enjoy!